shape what the author innovatively theorizes as the archive's hermeneutic dispositif. Archival Film Curatorship offers film and preservation scholars a unique take on the shifting definitions, histories, and uses of the medium of film by those tasked with preserving and presenting it to new digital-age audiences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aFilm Studies. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 4aMedia Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh  aFilm Archives and Museums, Early and Silent Cinema, Film Curatorship, Digital Turn, Film Historiography.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048555741?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048555741zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048555741/original  a978-3-11-102374-8 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7 EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4 EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA